This map is made by me, mainly after passing through the hall of the central trainstation in Groningen (city in the Netherlands). Its architecture fascinated me, and therefore I decided to try and make a Counter-Strike map around it. 

The hall has been reconstructed using pictures and a sketch (see screenshots, note: drawing not made by me). The area around it is purely fictional and adjusted to fit a CS Counter-strike map.

It is currently in development and halfway done (T-side done, CT side just a box :P). The roof is still to come as well. See the development tab above for more pictures and the whole process. 

It has been uploaded for testing and fun, to let the public see the map, test it and tell me what I can improve :)

It is made for max 20 players (10vs10, obviously), but it has not yet been fully optimized in brushwork and VISleafs (for those who know what I mean), I cannot guarantee optimal fps in large groups. In addition, it works nicely in 3vs3ish as well.

Known bugs at the moment: 
# In the secret passage vent from the storage room to the upstairs office, people can have problems climbing the stairs and jumping from it. Face the stairs, press crouch and jump to get there.
# When 1vs1 Bot remain after a while (T bot camping the Hostage Rescue zone and CT bot rescuing the hostages, they might get stuck and look at a wall for a few minutes before continuing to their confrontation. 
# Lag problems due to no complete optimization

Have fun testing and debugging. :D

..:: CENTRAL STATION

Created by Nathan "nay0r" | www.map-central.co.uk

Nav by Peter "Barndoor" Calvert 
http://www.tequilakawa.plus.com/ 

Apart of the Dimension Studios Network
http://www.dimensionstudios.org

In the year 1934 Central Station Bridge was
Reconstructed and widened after many years
In service between Liverpool and Manchester 
In 2005 the station was closed due to a new line 
Opening at Bank quay station, although after the closure
Terrorists ransacked one of the few remaining 
Trains and took control of the station and
Members of the public who were in the local area
What they donâ€™t know is a specialized squad has 
Been sent in. Also in a near by house they have
Hacked central stations CCTV cameras and have rigged
Up a monitor overlooking the station, although 
Connection is not 100% clear, it should aid in
Locating any suspects

Rescue points are located at central stations
Subway exit and outside near the northern petrol
Pumps, safely navigate hostages to the parked vans

Email: nayisdeath@hotmail.com

..:: Overview

Cs_central started out in March 2006, And ive
been on and off with the project, initally it was
meant to be a rebuild of an old 1.6 map known as
cs_intercept but after some thought I changed it 
into what is now known as cs_central.
It was meant to be a piece of art at first, it was a test
to see what i could do with the source engine, but after
constructing a major part of the bridge and station 
( which is based on a true place where i live )
I then decided to try and make it into something playable 
with reasonable frame rates.

The train bridge and passing road and the station itself are 
all based around the real place but the petrol station in real
life is just an old long distant car park looking over the town.

The beach area is a large outdoor area with a bus station,
When i started the project it was acutally the back of the shopping centre
which has recently recieved millions of pounds of rebuilding work 
to make it into a 21st century bus station

and the edge of the road in cs_central which points in the direction of the
old cottage near the petrol station runs to the rubgy stadium.

			..:: DETAILED MAP INFORMATION

: 	The map comes with LDR and HDR cubemaps compiled.
: 	Radar Overview.
: 	Highly Tuned Bot Navigation File.
: 	All Custom content is embedded into the BSP. ( 68.4mb )
: 	The map has a point_servercommand to allow servers to automatically
  	let users download the map.
:	The dynamic camera does seem to make users loose a fair bit of performance
	when running around, once it is destroyed it returns to normal
:	The Stations toilets can be entered, 
:	Overhead powerlines are Electrical So dont touch them when jumping 
	on top of the parked train.
:	Lightmaps are only Lower on the station, rest of the map are 
	generally higher than default.

			..:: Credits

Thanks to Valve, I used there Coke machine from de_nuke.
Plus The custom soundscape i used in cs_central is built around 
serveral of the official maps, including assault/port/office and train

			..:: Performance

I know the map is not amazing in terms of performance, This is 
because i didnt plan the map very well from the begining as explained above
but i believe it gets as good as it can for whats being rendered.
I spent various amounts of weeks hinting and using areaportals and window portals
to optimize the map, and using nodraw and func_detail.
worked  on this one for 2 days straight and 3 hours of sleep. hope it accepts hehe.

At that, here are some errors that i don't need told to me.

**ERROR! (if you can fix these and tell me how i will put you in the credits)

**There is a tiny brush by the ladder on the ceiling in the watery pipey room, it wasn't rendering right because it was off grid so i moved it on grid and now it doesn't line up, barely noticeable (tell me if you think otherwise)

**On the helicopter outside all the textures are wrong. They all need to be rotated some degree or another, I'll get around to it eventually

**The walls are to thin!!! same with the ceilings/floors =(( this causes the ability to be able to see guns and people through them (sometimes) just don't hide where you think you will be seen.

**Props cast shadows on walls in the floor below (so do people and their corpses). I think i know how to fix this but it doesn't affect the game play so I've been ignoring it

**People fall through props (like all the barrels, is there a way to make them myself where people won't?)

**props- how many is too many?

**A red light shines through the floor outside the compound (can't figure out a fix blocklight=fail)

**Textures on the archways! IF anyone knows of a better texture that could be used, or for that matter better textures to be use ANYWHERE in the map, let me know, I will gladly change any textures in the map if i think it will look better

IF theres anything i missed putting into this please tell me, if i think you can help me I will give the .VMF(T?) out on request, please help me make it better! or at least make my next one better

This is my first map, and is alright I think. The detail isn't too great but it is just a Beta, and the gameplay is really good. There are many different passageways, and lots of different strategies to use. The bridge down the middle can be quick escape, but there is no cover from many sniping spots. Sometimes the games can last quite a while with all the different routes (especially if the bots get stuck in the water). There are two ladders to get out of the water on the wall of the little  platforms that stick out from the side, and another two vines to climb up on closer to the center (all vines are climable on this map). The hostage rescue point is the top floor of the side that the Counter-Terrorists spawn on. That rope like thing is also climable, but the AI seems to just disregard it. Overall it is a great map for medium/large size groups.

#### Calm Village Pro - Hostage Rescue

##### By Will2k

cs-calm-pro is a remastered version of my earlier source map cs-calm-source released in 2010 (can be found here http://www.gamebanana.com/maps/151858)

While the map was nice and fun to play and was featured on several servers, I never felt that it got the attention that it deserved fom my side. After all, cs-calm-source was itself a quick remake of my map cs-calm for CS 1.6 from 2003. It actually helped me get back to business after I stopped mapping for almost 7 years. 

Many people also indicated that the map needs some adjustments and more details; so after releasing de-spezia last month, I went back to cs-calm-source and what actually started as slight modification ended up as redesigning and rebuilding around 70% of the map from scratch :)

New areas and routes were added, old layout was heavily modified; textures, lighting and props were completely replaced and the overall map area was slightly increased to ensure smoother gameplay.

As usual, the map is fully optimized to ensure fluid gameplay and consistent high FPS.

The map has:

- 32 spawn points (16 vs 16) I considered 64 spawn points but I think it would be too much for the size of the map.
- radar overview
- 3D skybox
- Soundscapes
- custom textures and models
- Nav file with place names

All the custom resources (except the nav) are embedded in the bsp.

For installation, simply extract the 4 files in the zip archive (bsp, nav and 2 txt files) to your \Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps folder.


I really hope you enjoy this map as much as I did creating and testing it.
Comments and constructive feedback are always welcome.

Will2k

October 22, 2011

The basic idea of CS_Cabaret is that a group of Terrorists have taken control of a gentlemens club, while taking a few hostages at the same time. Its up to the Counter-Terrorists to break in and save the day. Theres quite a few entrances on all different sides of the club, allowing both quick entry and quick exit for both teams while providing both outdoor long range combat and indoor CQB action.

Cabaret has been heavily balanced and fine tuned to make sure that no team has a clear advantage, and that each team has equal opportunities at victory. Through countless hours of playtesting with both humans and bots, the map has proved to be amazingly balanced for a assault-styled map.

The custom hostage models included with the map are strippers, as it definetly suites the map more than the original (and boring) worker hostages. Theres also a ton of custom textures, models and sounds which are completely new, so it definetly gives the map a unique look and feel which is unlike any other map around. The downside of all the custom content is that t he filesize of the map grows considerably. The materials, models and sounds account for about 20mb out of the 60mb bsp, while almost all the rest of the filesize is due to HDR lighting (it nearly triples the filesize). Its good to use new technology, though. I also spent alot of time making sure that the map was balanced for each side, allowing fair and maybe even competitive gameplay. I tested the map with both human players and bots for balance, and after lots of tweaking, the map eventually became even.

Speaking of bots, there is a heavily tweaked .nav file included in the map which I created almost from the ground up, which will make those with unstable internet connections happy as the bots preform quite well around the map. The only issue which I couldent figure out a way to fix (but did manage to lessen its occurrence) was how the bots interact with doors. Sometimes theyll get caught on the door and wait for a few seconds before managing to get by. Since the hostages also use the .nav file aswell, they run around very well and will rarely get stuck on anything (unless you decide to lead them through the entire building while running as fast as possible).

Recomended Players: 6-20 Maximum: 40

The zip archive must be unzipped into the directory Steam/Steamapps/youraccount/counter-strike source/cstrike respecting the folder names.

All models, materials, sounds, nav mesh and additional elements are embedded into the bsp.

The files navplace.db, cstrike_english.txt and cstrike_french.txt are optional and the map can work without them. However, they allow more appropriate place names to be displayed under the radar and in the chat. Keep in mind that installing these files will prevent the game from having access to the files bearing the same names in the gcf (cache) and to the potential modifications that Valve can make on them.If you're unsure, unzip only the .bsp
